t half is full of scenes that involve both of them. The story goes into a flashback where Kamal Haasan and Vidhubala are a couple where Kamal Haasan suspects Vidhubala and kills her. Shoba reincarnates as Vidhubala and tells the truth to Kamal Haasan. Upon hearing the story Kamal Haasan gets himself killed by running towards a lorry. The film ends in a sad note with both Kamal Haasan and Shoba dying at the end.',150,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjI5MWVmNzgtMTI2My00YmFmLWI5N2EtN2YyZDU4NDI3NDQxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEzOTQwNTY@.jpg',1977,'Drama','Malayalam','K.S. Sethumadhavan','Joseph Anand, N. Govindankutty, K.S. Sethumadhavan','K.S.R. Moorthy, K.S. Sethumadhavan','M.S. Viswanathan','Marcus Bartley','T.R. Srinivasalu'),('Nirakudam',5,'Dharmapalan (Adoor Bhasi) and his younger brother Satyapalan (Nellikkodu Bhaskaran) live together along with their families. The big happy joint family comprises the childless Dharmapalan and Satyapalan who has two sons - Devan (Kamal Haassan) and Rajan (Sudheer) who is studying in a college in the city. Devan\'s left leg and hand were paralysed due to an electric shock while he was still a child. Dharmapalan\'s wife Bhargavi (Sukumari) is jealous of Satyapalan\'s family and invites her brother\'s children Prabhakaran (Jose Prakash) and Usha (Reena) to live with them. Prabhakaran plans and organises Usha\'s marriage with Rajan. He also creates a rift between the brother\'s families, ensuring that the families separate. Satyapalan and his wife Sati (Kaviyoor Ponnamma) find it difficult to find a bride for Devan. But Santha (Sridevi), an orphan maid, volunteers to marry Devan. Eventually Devan and Rajan are blessed with children. Prabhakaran borrows money from Bhargavi and Rajan to invest in a dance show business in the city with Margarette (Kadeeja) and her daughter (Usha Rani). Prabhakaran loses heavily in the dance shows. Rajan had taken money from his office and is under pressure to return the money. In the meanwhile Santha decides to get Devan treated for his handicap and they come to the city. Bhargavi and Rajan demand that Prabhakaran returns their money. Prabhakaran, desperate to make money, snatches Devan\'s child and tries to organise a circus show involving an elephant and Devan\'s child. Both Devan and Santha reach the venue. Devan, desperate to save his child from the elephant, comes in contact with a live wire and gets an electric shock. As a result of the shock he recovers and saves his child. A happy ending to the family drama that upholds family values. Prabhakaran is arrested. The separated families of Dharmapalan and Satyapalan are united and they live together happily.',NULL,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjc5ZjdhNzItOWYxZC00YmYxLTk2MDEtNzU3OWU3YWQ5MTQwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEzOTQwNTY@.jpg',1977,'Drama','Malayalam','A. Bhimsingh','A. Bhimsingh, Surasu','Baby','Jaya-Vijaya','U. Rajagopal, G. Vittal Rao','K. Sankunny'),('Ashtamangalyam',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDJiOGVmYTItY2QyNy00MzUwLTlhYTgtNDllNTUwYTM1NTVkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEzOTQwNTY@.jpg',1977,'Drama','Malayalam','P. Gopikumar','P.K. Abraham, P.K. Abraham','K.H. Khan Sahib','M.K. Arjunan','Vipindas','K. Sankunny'),('Kabita',6.8,'Kabita is a 1977 Indian Bengali film directed by Bharat Shamsher and Jung Bahadur Rana. The film stars Mala Sinha,Kamal Hassan and Ranjit Mallick in the lead roles. Music of the film was composed by Salil Chowdhury.',146,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMGUyNDcyOWMtYTAyZS00OWZlLTgwNzgtMjAzNmI5ZTkxYTE2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEzOTQwNTY@.jpg',1977,'Drama, Family','Bangla','Bharat Shumsher Jung Bahadur Rana','Bharat Shumsher Jung Bahadur Rana, Bharat Shumsher Jung Bahadur Rana',NULL,'Salil Choudhury','K.A. Reza','Amiya Mukherjee'),('Unnai Sutrum Ulagam',7.3,NULL,NULL,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTFkZmExOGItOWYxOS00NTcyLWE1MTgtMmEzZTYzYTU4MDljXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEzOTQwNTY@.jpg',1977,'Drama','Tamil','G. Subramanya Reddiar','G. Subramanya Reddiar',NULL,'Sh